@wohali you mean when we add another clustering ~later~layer? ;D

This needs conceptual approval before moving on.

Should this approach be acceptable, I'd also re-enable the design doc filter optimisation  the same way.

@jaydoane After having been an 80-column adherent for 30 years now (I started on VT-52 terminals connected to a PDP-11/34A), I'm growing more in love with slightly longer line length.

I want to propose [Black](https://github.com/ambv/black) for our Python code, which adopts an 88-character limit. They have a [researched answer as to why 90-ish is probably better than 80](https://github.com/ambv/black#line-length), complete with YouTube video.

Over in apache/couchdb-documentation, due to limitations of the ReStructuredText parser and some very long URL references we can't line wrap without breaking the syntax, we've had to recently relax line length from 80 to 90 for similar reasons.

@davisp @jaydoane how would you feel about 90?

The issue stems from : https://github.com/apache/couchdb/pull/1085
and specifically : https://github.com/apache/couchdb/pull/1085/files#diff-9d6b535641fc74e993a6c0a246313619R102

@jiangphcn added the {offset, null} there which breaks the follow up bit where it defaults to 0 if the key isn't present.

It's a meaningless value either way - but it did change. We disagree with the Ektorp author; we believe it should be possible to disable asserting JSON types in that client.

@jiangphcn are you able to look at this one? Perhaps we should remove 'offset' from view response in all cases?

@WillemvdW This is the wrong place for this discussion - please take it to one of these other options:

* The user mailing list. Signup instructions are [here](http://couchdb.apache.org/#mailing-lists)
* The Slack/IRC chat room. Joining instructions are [here](http://couchdb.apache.org/#chat)
